{
  "info": {
    "name": "Document Management System API",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the Document Management System. All endpoints are prefixed with http://localhost:8000/api/\n\n## Authentication\n\n**Knox token authentication** – Each login creates a new Knox auth token. Send `Authorization: Token <token>` header.\n\nThe login response returns a `token` (auto-saved for subsequent requests), `expiry` (ISO datetime when token expires), and `user` object. Logout deletes the current token; Logout All deletes all tokens for the user.\n\nAll user-related fields (`uploaded_by`, `shared_by`, `shared_with_user`, `created_by`, `members`) return nested `{id, user: {id, username, email}}` details.\n\n## Variables\n\n| Variable      | Description                                 |\n|---------------|---------------------------------------------|\n| `base_url`    | Server URL (default http://localhost:8000)  |\n| `auth_token`  | Auth token – auto-set by Login script       |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', jsonData.token);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"your_username\",\n  \"password\": \"your_password\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login", ""]
            },
            "description": "Login with username/password. Returns:\n- `token`       – Knox auth token (auto-saved to auth_token variable)\n- `expiry`      – ISO datetime when the token expires\n- `user`        – Object with `id` and `username`\n\nThe auth_token is auto-saved to the collection variable for subsequent requests.\n\nEach login creates a new Knox AuthToken; multiple simultaneous sessions are supported."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Token {{auth_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/logout/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "logout", ""]
            },
            "description": "Logout – deletes only the current Knox token (the one used in the Authorization header), not all sessions."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout All",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Token {{auth_token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/logout-all/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "logout-all", ""]
            },
            "description": "Logout from all sessions – deletes every Knox auth token for the current user."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
